        p.title-2 Artistic Collaboration
        p.paragraph On a time constraint, we grappled with the challenge of executing three scenes in the script, each illustrating the intricate process of carving a wooden Buddha statue from its inception to completion—a task that typically spans several months.The artisans amongst the monks volunteered to have three separate statues crafted for us, each at a different stage of the carving process. This contribution to our film stood as a powerful testament to the way artistic collaboration can transcend the boundaries of language and culture.

